text:
There’s no way to add a controlling field for a global theme setting hidden subfield is there? i.e. I have a checkbox item field, and if true I want to change a property in another field’s hidden_subfield to false. It looks like you can’t do something like
```"visibility": {
  "hidden_subfields": {
    "size": "theme.blah.enable_some_setting"
  }
}```
:disappointed:

Anyone know why these aren’t working in the global theme options?
```"inherited_value": {
  "default_value_path": "theme.colors.secondary"
}

"inherited_value": {
  "property_value_paths": {
    "color": "theme.colors.secondary.color"
  }
}```
I’m referencing `theme.colors.secondary.color` in the CSS and it works fine.
